Phase 5 — L2 Cognitive Wiring (Think → Act → Approve → Execute)

Goal: Intelligence exists ONLY in L2, and actions are approval-gated.

5.1 Evidence Drawer (L2)
	•	fetch Spine entity snapshots
	•	fetch linked Context items
	•	fetch lineage + audit chain
	•	show provenance of every claim

5.2 Think Engine (L2)
	•	produce: summary, signals, insights
	•	every insight has evidence_refs + confidence

5.3 Act Engine (L2)
	•	proposes ActionPlan (tool calls + payload preview)
	•	runs policy checks (allow/deny/allow_with_approval)

5.4 Approvals / Decisions (L2)
	•	approve/reject/edit with RBAC
	•	decision record is mandatory
	•	only after approval → emit ExecutionRequest

5.5 Execution Plane (L0 tool plane / connector hub)
	•	receives ExecutionRequest
	•	re-check policy + scope + token
	•	executes tool write
	•	returns outcome → stored as audit/outcome and linked to trace_id

Definition of Done
	•	L2 can generate recommendation with evidence
	•	approval required for write
	•	approved action executes via connectors
	•	outcome stored + learnable

