Phase 6 — Goals & Dual-Context Metrics (Your new non-negotiable)

Goal: Every metric must map to a goal (vendor + client + personal).

6.1 Add SSOT objects (L3 Spine)
	•	Goal (vendor/client/personal scope)
	•	Metric (must have goal_refs[])
	•	Outcome (goal attainment evidence)
	•	Intervention (approved actions linked to goals)

6.2 Enforce “Metric Validity Policy” (L3 + L2)
	•	L3: reject or quarantine metrics without goal_refs (or mark invalid)
	•	L2: never surface unmapped metrics; instead propose goal mapping
	•	L1: shows only goal-linked metrics and progress state

6.3 Dual-context impact scoring (L2)

Each recommendation includes:
	•	vendor_goal_impact (ARR/NRR/Retention/Expansion/CAC)
	•	client_goal_impact (Outcome/ROI/Efficiency/Goal attainment)
	•	evidence for both

Definition of Done
	•	a metric cannot appear unless linked to a goal
	•	L2 recommendations always show impact on both masters
	•	L1 shows goal progress without cognitive overlays

